import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('country').count().sort_values(by='iata', ascending=False).reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['country'], data['iata'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports by country?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Country')
    plt.ylabel('Number of airports')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data.groupby('state')['iata'].count().sort_values(ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,6))
    ax.bar(state_counts.index, state_counts.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('State/Province')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Airports')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of airports by state/province?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
